PICK OF THE WEEK 
The West Coast premiere of "The Downside" by Richard Dresser is at the Pasadena 
Playhouse, 39 S. El Molino Ave., through Jan. 14. 
The comedy involves the antics of a marketing firm that is rushing a new 
anti-stress product onto the market. Kenneth Frankel is director and the stars 
are John Getz, Kelly Connell, above left, Megan Mullaly, center, Meagan Fay, 
Carl Riggiardo, James Eckhouse, above right, Eddie Jones, Paul Guilfoyle and 
Matt Salinger. 
Performances are at 8 p.m. Tuesdays through Fridays, 5 and 9 p.m. Saturdays and 
2 and 7 p.m. Sundays. Tickets are $28.50. 
